│ guard condition to skip processing when `ExitSCEV` is                       │
│ `SCEVCouldNotCompute`.\n\n5. Conclusion:\n\nBy adding a check for           │
│ `SCEVCouldNotCompute` before calling `getMinusSCEV`, we prevent the crash   │
│ and allow the expander to fall back to other expansion strategies when SCEV │
│ analysis fails for complex pointer types. This is a defensive programming   │
│ fix that maintains the existing behavior for valid cases while preventing   │
│ the assertion failure for invalid cases."})                                 │
